cff-version: 1.2.0
title: "SKI Framework: Sovereign Knowledge Intelligence — neuro-symbolic AI compliance for regulated industries"
message: "If you reference the SKI Framework in academic or professional work, please cite as below."
type: software
authors:
  - given-names: "KpiFinity"
    family-names: "Inc."
    affiliation: "KpiFinity Inc."
    website: "https://kpifinity.com"
repository-code: "https://github.com/kpifinity/ski-framework"
url: "https://skiframework.org"
abstract: >
  An open neuro-symbolic architecture for AI compliance in regulated industries.
  The specification (CC BY 4.0) defines a sovereign-by-construction runtime in
  which a knowledge-graph-grounded local language model is the primary reasoner
  on every verdict and an independent symbolic verifier cross-checks the
  formalizable subset of each rule. Every verdict carries verifiable
  provenance: signed model weights, signed knowledge-graph version, signed
  language-model transcript, knowledge-graph citations, and the symbolic
  verifier's per-assertion result, all hash-chained into an append-only audit
  ledger. The reference implementation (Apache 2.0) implements
  specification v3.0 per RFC 0002: the KG-grounded sovereign LLM is the
  primary reasoner on every verdict, the Symbolic Verifier mechanically
  cross-checks the formalizable subset, and the strict Risk-Tier
  Governor reads the tier from the KG itself (the caller cannot
  self-declare).
keywords:
  - compliance
  - regulated industries
  - sovereign AI
  - neuro-symbolic
  - knowledge graph
  - verifiable inference
  - audit defensibility
  - on-premise LLM
  - SKI Framework
